## Project Structure
```
packages/
  functions/src/
    handlers/      orchestrate ONLY — no business logic
    controllers/   HTTP adapter: validate → service → presenter → response
    services/      business logic; combine multiple repos; 3rd-party APIs
    repositories/  ONE Firestore collection each — NEVER mix collections
    presenters/    format output data
    helpers/       pure single-purpose utilities (no DB, no API)
    const/         constants grouped by feature
    config/        configuration
  assets/src/      React admin (Polaris pages, hooks, contexts, loadables)
  scripttag/       storefront script injection (lightweight)
```

## Core Rules (apply everywhere)
- **Layers, one-way imports:** handlers/controllers → services → repositories. Never
  repo→service, repo→repo, or business logic in a handler/repo.
- **Multi-tenant:** every Firestore query/mutation scoped by `shopId` (first param).
- **Repository = one collection.** Collection name inline as `const COLLECTION_NAME`.
- **Response format:** `{success: true, data}` or `{success: false, error}`.
- **Request body:** `ctx.req.body` (NOT `ctx.request.body`).
- **Webhooks respond < 5s** — queue heavy work (Cloud Tasks / Pub/Sub), never inline.
  `await publishTopic` for reliability — no fire-and-forget.
- **Firestore:** batch ≤ 500, `in` ≤ 30, `.empty` not `.size`, filter early with `where`,
  select only needed fields, aggregates for count/sum/avg. Compound queries need an index
  in `firestore-indexes/{collection}.json` (`yarn firestore:build`).
- **Async:** `Promise.all` for independent ops; never `await` in a loop.

## Naming & Style
- `camelCase` vars/functions/props · `PascalCase` classes/React components ·
  `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` constants.
- Functions start with verbs; booleans prefix `is/has`.
- Prefer `const`; `===`; async/await; early return (minimize `else`); single responsibility.
- Functions with >3 params take a destructured object.
- Keep files under ~200 lines; JSDoc on public service/handler functions.

## Frontend (React / Polaris)
- One component per file (PascalCase filename), functional components only.
- Polaris v12+ components; navigation via `url` prop (NOT `onClick` + `window.open`).
- React Context over prop drilling; custom hooks for reusable logic; BEM CSS classes.
- Lazy-load pages via loadables.

## Security
- Never commit credentials/secrets or a `*.trycloudflare.com` dev tunnel URL.
- Ownership check before any resource mutation (`if (resource.shopID !== shopID) throw 403`).
- Verify webhook HMAC. Sanitize/parameterize all inputs and DB/BigQuery queries.
- `target="_blank"` always needs `rel="noopener noreferrer"`.

## Pre-commit
- `yarn lint` before commit, `yarn test` before push. Never ignore failing tests.
- Conventional commit messages; focused, atomic commits.
